  "text": "The participants valued humour as a way to express themselves without being antagonistic and as welcomed distraction online. Humour may be useful when designing for groups with low political engagement by adding entertainment value to the debate. For example, applications that allow the easy generation of 'memes' could act as a simple way of creating discussion within the social group of a politically disengaged viewer. Past research has noted playful aspects of online political discourse [CITATION_1] but it has overlooked its potential to make politics feel more accessible by the wider public. Future research may investigate whether humour can engage politically disengaged viewers.",
